Chilean Stocks: Cap, Cencosud, Cervecerias Unidas and Falabella

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-04T21:01:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/chilean-stocks-cap-cencosud-cervecerias-unidas-and-falabella.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:14 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 3.9 percent to 4,142.38, its biggest
fall since October 2008.  Cap SA (CAP)   slumped 3.8 percent to 19,646 pesos, its
biggest fall in seven weeks. Chile’s largest steel producer and
iron miner fell in line with the price of base metals, which
retreated on signs that the global economic recovery is
stalling, damping the demand outlook for commodities.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC),  Latin America ’s third-largest
retailer by sales, fell 4.6 percent to 2,811.2 pesos, its lowest
price in almost a year. Consumer demand growth will tend to
normalize in Chile after strong growth, Chile’s central bank
president Jose de Gregorio said in a conference today in
Santiago.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)  , Chile’s largest retailer by
market value, retreated 4.1 percent to 4,087 pesos, its third
day of losses.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU CC) retreated 3.6 percent
to 4,818 pesos, its eighth day of losses.  Chile ’s largest brewer
had second-quarter net income of 10.2 billion pesos ($22
million), down from 20.6 billion pesos a year earlier, according
to data posted on the website of Chile’s securities regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
